# Themes and Styling System

The NoteToMP plugin has a sophisticated theming system to ensure content renders properly in WeChat:

## Theme Management
- [assets.ts](mdc:src/assets.ts) handles loading and managing themes
- Themes are stored in the `assets/themes/` directory
- Default theme defined in [default-theme.ts](mdc:src/default-theme.ts)

## Code Highlighting
- Code syntax highlighting themes in `assets/highlights/`
- Default highlight style in [default-highlight.ts](mdc:src/default-highlight.ts)
- Uses highlight.js for syntax highlighting

## CSS Processing
- [inline-css.ts](mdc:src/inline-css.ts) handles inlining CSS for WeChat compatibility
- Transforms external CSS into inline styles for content export
- CSS is processed and embedded directly in HTML elements

## Custom Styles
- Users can create custom CSS in a `custom.css` file
- Plugin UI defined in [styles.css](mdc:styles.css)
- Custom styles can be enabled/disabled in settings
